<item>
            <title>[SPARK-25535] Work around bad error checking in commons-crypto</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25535</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The commons-crypto library used for encryption can get confused when certain errors happen; that can lead to crashes since the Java side thinks the ciphers are still valid while the native side has already cleaned up the ciphers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can work around that in Spark by doing some error checking at a higher level.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
